<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFBFEF7CFF42F9CCFC73F828" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBFEF7CFF42F9CCFC4CF90F" blockId="23.[151,1436,1584,1936]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBFEF7CFF42F9CCFEE7F92B" bold="true" box="[199,338,1657,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the first record of the species since its original description. The species is mostly green coloured, with a tricolour stripe band (red-white-red) on the pronotal carinae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBFEF7CFF42F974FBE8F8B8" blockId="23.[151,1436,1584,1936]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBFEF7CFF42F974FEEEF963" bold="true" box="[199,347,1729,1755]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFFBFEF7CFEEEF974FE40F964" box="[363,501,1729,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,184,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-29@24.[151,1436,181,1852]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 11. Calling songs of species of Aniarae species (Phaneropterinae) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A–B: Aniarella typica; C–E: Hyperophora brasiliensis; F–H: Hyperophora brasiliensis; A, C and F: sonogram of a sequence of echemes; D and G: sonogram of one echeme; B, D and H: spectrogram of the echeme highlighted in A, C and F, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550077/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 11A, B</figureCitation>
): Males stridulate at night, with echemes in a crescendo of intensity. The syllables are grouped in pairs, and sound is produced only in the closing stroke (hemisyllables).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBFEF7CFF42F8BFFD30F89B" blockId="23.[151,1436,1584,1936]" box="[199,645,1801,1828]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBFEF7CFF42F8BFFE1EF89B" box="[199,427,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 14.2 ± 0.005 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBFEF7CFF42F898FE4BF8FF" blockId="23.[151,1436,1584,1936]" box="[199,510,1837,1864]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBFEF7CFF42F898FEF5F8FF" box="[199,320,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 1.1 ± 0.02 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBFEF7CFF42F8E7FCC6F8D4" blockId="23.[151,1436,1584,1936]" box="[199,883,1873,1900]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBFEF7CFF42F8E7FE9BF8D3" box="[199,302,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Duration</emphasis>
: Echeme: 17.4 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFFBFEF7CFE71F8E7FD8CF8D4" box="[500,569,1874,1900]" degrees="10.7" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" precision="5555" value="-10.7">10.7 s</geoCoordinate>
; Syllable: 0.003 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFFBFEF7CFC88F8E7FCDBF8D4" box="[781,878,1874,1900]" degrees="0.0004" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" precision="5" value="-4.0E-4">0.0004 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBFEF7CFF42F8C3FC73F828" blockId="23.[151,1436,1584,1936]" box="[199,966,1909,1936]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBFEF7CFF42F8C3FEEAF837" box="[199,351,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 0.16 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFFBFEF7CFDA2F8C3FDCFF828" box="[551,634,1910,1936]" degrees="0.003" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" precision="55" value="-0.003">0.003 s</geoCoordinate>
; Pair of syllables: 1.5 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFFBFEF7CFC0FF8C3FC74F828" box="[906,961,1910,1936]" degrees="0.3" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" precision="5555" value="-0.3">0.3 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
